It will work with default `esMduleInterop`:
```ts
import DurationUnitFormat from 'intl-unofficial-duration-unit-format';

const duration = new DurationUnitFormat();
const parts = duration.formatToParts(90);

console.log(parts);
```
compiles and runs fine.

Not that this package has invalid `package.json` declaration and needs to be updated itself:
```bash
Error [ERR_INVALID_PACKAGE_TARGET]: Invalid "exports" main target "dist/cjs/duration-unit-format.cjs.js" defined in the package config C:\develop\tests\node_modules\intl-unofficial-duration-unit-format\package.json; targets must start with "./"
```
